 Summer Robertson from Shrewsbury died after being overpowered by fierce currents off a picturesque beach in December near Kenton-on-Sea .
Miss Robertson was with three other British members of a team that had completed a 10-week charity adventure at a remote camping resort .
Another volunteer , 19-year-old Alice Barnett got into difficulties in the water .
Her parents have been remembering their daughter , who died while on a trip of a lifetime working with deprived youngsters .